{
  "stem": "9168.7",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- when I went to the House, I made a commitment to myself that I would not stay more than 10 years, whereas others stay to the end of their lives sometimes.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I had discussed the stress of the work, and I was a-- a chief reporter over 19 people-- seven other reporters of debates, eight transcribers, and four clerks.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was a very stressful job, especially when we worked 12 hours a day.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so I came back in 1982.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in 1983, my judge whom I worked for here in Denver when I went to Congress, Judge Robert T.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Kingsley, who is deceased, asked me if I would go back with him in the Denver court system for the two years until he retired in 1985.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But it was-- whenever anyone knew that I worked on the Nuremberg war trials, they would ask me if I would speak about it.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I did, in a very relaxed kind of setting, just storytelling what I remembered.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And from 1985 on, I became very aware then of all the Holocaust denial.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was 1989, 1988 where we had a teacher right here at Hinkley High School in Aurora denying that the Holocaust ever occurred.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then I decided that I thought that it was time for me to start putting together a serious presentation.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I had all of these files I brought with me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I was, you know, loading myself with information.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I had all these pictures that I brought from Nuremberg, Associated Press black-and-white glossies.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I had acquired others from people who knew I reported the trials.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So I really started putting it together-- 10 years now.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
